TinyMCE Rails Plugin
========

The Tiny MCE Plugin will allow you to easily add in the tiny mce editor 
(http://tinymce.moxiecode.com/) into any of your rails apps.

USAGE AND INSTALLATION
======================

1. rake tinymce:install
2. Put <%= include_tiny_mce {:options} %> somewhere in your layout or view file, preferably in your <head> section

== CONFIGURATION OPTIONS

A list of configuration options can be viewed at: 
  http://wiki.moxiecode.com/index.php/TinyMCE:Configuration#General


- :mode # defaults to 'specific_textareas'
- :class # defaults to 'editor'
- :theme # defaults to 'advanced'
- :convert_urls # defaults to false
- :fonts # defaults to standard serif/sans-serif fonts
- :text_colors # defaults to standard primary colors
- :buttons # defaults to standard font buttons
- :toolbar_location # defaults to 'top'
